                            <comment id="16684608" author="udim" created="Tue, 13 Nov 2018 01:51:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The script was pruning old networks (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-4051&quot; title=&quot;python postcommit failure in docker-compose&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BEAM-4051&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BEAM-4051&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) but leftover containers still referenced them.&lt;br/&gt;
This is a problem if you run `docker-compose up` twice in a row and the leftover container is reused,&lt;br/&gt;
but it&apos;s a rare occurrence since containers get rebuilt whenever a change is made.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16685949" author="udim" created="Wed, 14 Nov 2018 00:52:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Previous theory was wrong, but the PR is beneficial for running the test locally and general cleanup of docker-compose artifacts.&lt;br/&gt;
New PR #7025 should work (for real), by disabling the namenode&apos;s reverse DNS lookup check.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
